Industrial Business Rules

Version:
1.0

Status:
Official

Project:
NEXOTFE ERP Industrial

==========================================================
PURPOSE
==========================================================

This document defines the official industrial business philosophy of NEXOTFE.

Every AI participating in the project must understand how a real manufacturing company operates before implementing software.

Business knowledge is mandatory.

Technical knowledge alone is not sufficient.

==========================================================
INDUSTRY FIRST
==========================================================

NEXOTFE does not force companies to adapt to software.

The software must adapt to the industrial reality.

Every implementation must faithfully represent real manufacturing processes.

==========================================================
BUSINESS BEFORE SOFTWARE
==========================================================

Every business rule originates from a real industrial activity.

Software exists only to organize, automate and improve those activities.

Technology is never the objective.

Business is.

==========================================================
MASTER DATA
==========================================================

Master Data represents stable business information.

Examples:

Customers

Suppliers

Employees

Products

Raw Materials

Resources

Resource Groups

Master Data supports every operational process.

==========================================================
TRANSACTIONAL DATA
==========================================================

Transactional data represents business events.

Examples:

Projects

Quotations

Commercial Proposals

Purchase Requests

Purchase Orders

Inventory Movements

Production Orders

Every transaction must be traceable.

==========================================================
CUSTOM MANUFACTURING
==========================================================

NEXOTFE is primarily designed for custom manufacturing.

Every project may be unique.

Products may never be manufactured twice.

Engineering is part of the commercial process.

==========================================================
PROJECT PHILOSOPHY
==========================================================

Projects are the center of industrial operations.

Projects generate:

Engineering.

Products.

Quotations.

Commercial Proposals.

Purchasing.

Manufacturing.

Planning.

Every project has its own identity.

==========================================================
RAW MATERIALS
==========================================================

Raw materials represent physical inventory.

Each material has:

Description.

Commercial characteristics.

Inventory information.

Approved suppliers.

Storage location.

Business information must never be duplicated.

==========================================================
PRODUCTS
==========================================================

Products represent manufactured items.

A product may be:

Manufactured.

Developed.

Industrialized.

Resold.

Serviced.

Every product belongs to a business process.

==========================================================
SUPPLIERS
==========================================================

Suppliers are business partners.

One supplier may provide multiple materials.

The same material may have multiple approved suppliers.

Supplier selection is a purchasing decision.

==========================================================
PURCHASING
==========================================================

Purchasing exists to satisfy business demand.

Purchasing is driven by:

Projects.

Inventory.

Production.

Operational needs.

The buyer decides how to group purchase requests.

The software must support this decision.

==========================================================
RESOURCES
==========================================================

Resources represent productive capacity.

Examples:

Machines.

Workstations.

Equipment.

Resources have operational characteristics.

Resources are not employees.

==========================================================
EMPLOYEES
==========================================================

Employees represent people.

Resources represent production capacity.

These concepts must never be confused.

==========================================================
ROUTINGS
==========================================================

A routing defines how a product is manufactured.

It represents:

Operations.

Resources.

Estimated times.

Manufacturing sequence.

The routing represents knowledge.

Not production history.

==========================================================
SIMPLICITY
==========================================================

Industrial software must simplify complex operations.

Avoid unnecessary screens.

Avoid duplicated information.

Avoid unnecessary approvals.

Avoid unnecessary configuration.

==========================================================
USER PRODUCTIVITY
==========================================================

Every screen must reduce the user's work.

The software exists to accelerate industrial decisions.

Never increase operational effort.

==========================================================
LONG-TERM THINKING
==========================================================

Every implementation must remain useful for many years.

Avoid temporary business rules.

Avoid solutions that create future maintenance problems.

==========================================================
FINAL PRINCIPLE
==========================================================

NEXOTFE is an industrial engineering platform.

Every implementation must faithfully represent real industrial operations while keeping the user experience simple, fast and professional.